race.comment: MIRAVAL ROSE (3) classy mare proven at this level and distance range. First blemish of the prep when pressured early as fav for a tiring fourth over 1400m in the G2 Tristarc Stakes at Caulfield. There doesn't look to be as much pressure here and Rawiller will be out to pinch some cheap sectionals early. Can bounce back. MISS ROUMBINI (2) heavily supported in the G2 The Invitation at Randwick over 1400m, when raced keenly from a sticky gate to finish a poor eighth. Can tag the speed in this smaller contest and her form around Sepals has been franked. Respect. SNOW IN MAY (8) taken back from the awkward gate and presented at the right time when a plugging seventh over 1300m in the G3 Silver Eagle at Randwick. Can sit closer from the draw and take a hand in the finish. BAUHINIA (9) massive jump in grade when running out of her skin to secure fifth over 1400m at Randwick in the G2 Invitation. Look for her late. POUNCE (4) makes her Australian debut and must be kept safe.
